Response: # Debugging API Latency Increase After Adding Metrics

When API latency jumps significantly after adding metrics (80ms → 600ms), we need to systematically isolate whether the metrics collection itself is causing the slowdown or if it's revealing an underlying issue. Here's a debugging sequence to separate measurement overhead from real regression:

## 1. Baseline Confirmation
- Temporarily disable all new metrics to confirm the baseline performance returns to ~80ms
- If performance returns to normal, the metrics implementation is the likely culprit
- If performance remains slow, the metrics may have exposed an existing issue

## 2. Incremental Metrics Addition
- Re-enable metrics one by one or in logical groups
- Measure latency after each addition
- Identify which specific metric(s) correlate with the performance drop

## 3. Metrics Implementation Analysis
- For problematic metrics:
  - Check for synchronous operations blocking the main execution path
  - Look for expensive calculations or data processing
  - Examine frequency of collection (per-request vs. sampled)
  - Review any database or I/O operations triggered by metrics

## 4. Profiling
- Run CPU and memory profiling with and without metrics
- Compare flame graphs to identify new hot spots
- Look for unexpected function calls, garbage collection, or memory pressure

## 5. Metrics Collection Architecture Review
- Move metrics collection off the critical path (background processing)
- Consider buffering/batching metrics before processing
- Implement sampling for high-volume metrics (e.g., only measure 1% of requests)

## 6. Specific Checks
- Database connections: Check if metrics are creating new connections
- Logging: Ensure metrics aren't triggering excessive logging
- Third-party services: Verify if metrics call external services synchronously
- Lock contention: Look for thread synchronization issues

## 7. Optimization
- For necessary but expensive metrics:
  - Optimize the implementation
  - Reduce collection frequency
  - Move to asynchronous processing
  - Consider more efficient data structures

By following this systematic approach, you can determine whether the latency increase is due to measurement overhead (the metrics implementation itself) or if the metrics have revealed an actual performance regression in the underlying system.
